Write a class named Average that will keep track of the average of all integers passed to it. Use two members: The first one should be typestd::int32_t, and used to keep track of the sum of all the numbers you’ve seen so far. The second should keep track of how many numbers you’ve seen so far. You can divide them to find your average.a) Write all of the functions necessary for the following program to run:int main()
